Notice; absolutely there are definitely things in windows 8 that this, or any other known program cover up<br /><br />as for the start button itself.. it should be close.. but there are still slight differences lack of blur, buttons not perfectly aligned, and a context menu on right clicking the button for example<br /><br />Try it out though, and you should be pleasantly surprised <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />you can try it on windows 7 if you want to get a jumpstart on messing around (if your the type to). Or classic shell has a quick way to jump to the windows 7 style if you don't feel like customizing it<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Fri Dec 26, 2014 9:45 pm</p><hr />
