<title type="html"><![CDATA[Will my dad be able to tell the difference?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4051&amp;p=17157#p17157"><![CDATA[
We wanted to get my dad a laptop for christmas, he's quite used to windows 7, but the one laptop best buy had available with win7 was not in stock and I wanted to set it up for him before he drives back to saskatchewan.<br /><br />Best Buy offered to set up classic shell for us, and that seemed the easiest option, I find myself a bit anxious though, hopefully with some research I will be able to give him something that will be indistinguishable from his preferred windows 7 experience. If not I will have to purchase a copy of win7 from memory express and just hope that the dell laptop we got will accept a &quot;down&quot;grade.<br /><br />I'm not anticipating a problem, but I have been avoiding windows 8 like the plague after it made me feel useless, maybe I'm even more of a curmudgeon than my dad.<br /><br />Mostly he hoards his ripped video and music files, and stores them on dozens of external drives, so from what I've learned about classic shell, he shouldn't notice, but until I get the computer tomorrow and dig in for myself, I'll have to twiddle my thumbs and hope a few online guides will make my dad's christmas for me.<br /><br />Maybe the thread title should be added to the faq? <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6583">Holythirteen</a> — Fri Dec 26, 2014 3:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
